article above. My best general advice

01:04:16.240 --> 01:04:17.990
all revolves around the understanding

01:04:18.000 --> 01:04:19.589
the limitations of the scientific

01:04:19.599 --> 01:04:21.510
process. I've been very intentional with

01:04:21.520 --> 01:04:23.029
my wording. Reread these three

01:04:23.039 --> 01:04:24.789
paragraphs periodically until you see

01:04:24.799 --> 01:04:27.349
for yourself where they came from.

01:04:27.359 --> 01:04:30.069
Wasn't my first search result.

01:04:30.079 --> 01:04:34.470
Well, if you just look up CS231N,

01:05:04.470 --> 01:05:04.480
You can't understand how science is

01:05:04.480 --> 01:05:06.630
done. Can't understand papers without

01:05:06.640 --> 01:05:08.150
understanding the circumstances under

01:05:08.160 --> 01:05:10.069
which they are written. Most conferences

01:05:10.079 --> 01:05:12.069
enforce an 8 to nine page limit since

01:05:12.079 --> 01:05:13.829
most archive papers are also either

01:05:13.839 --> 01:05:15.430
published or were intended for

01:05:15.440 --> 01:05:17.109
publication. You'll notice that they are

01:05:17.119 --> 01:05:19.349
also 8 to nine pages. Why not shorter

01:05:19.359 --> 01:05:21.270
even for simple ideas? Because that is

01:05:21.280 --> 01:05:23.270
both an upper and lower limit. Writing a

01:05:23.280 --> 01:05:26.230
six-page paper will get you uh will

01:05:26.240 --> 01:05:28.950
normally get you rejected. Why do so

01:05:28.960 --> 01:05:31.029
many papers have excessively formalized

01:05:31.039 --> 01:05:32.549
math even when it's not relevant or

01:05:32.559 --> 01:05:34.390
helpful? Because reviewers like to see

01:05:34.400 --> 01:05:36.309
formulas. Also, some researchers just

01:05:36.319 --> 01:05:38.309
like writing them. Why is the paper

01:05:38.319 --> 01:05:40.150
missing X obvious ablation or control

01:05:40.160 --> 01:05:42.069
experiment? Because the overworked grad

01:05:42.079 --> 01:05:43.670
student who wrote it ran out of time in

01:05:43.680 --> 01:05:46.710
GPUs, mostly GPUs. Why aren't there more

01:05:46.720 --> 01:05:48.950
papers in X area? Reviewers don't like

01:05:48.960 --> 01:05:51.109
those. Oh, also plenty of papers are

01:05:51.119 --> 01:05:53.270
just wrong. But when two papers have

01:05:53.280 --> 01:05:55.029
appear to have directly contradictory

01:05:55.039 --> 01:05:57.109
results, that's probably be that's

01:05:57.119 --> 01:05:59.910
because they probably are. Don't trust

01:05:59.920 --> 01:06:01.990
prestige. You should care about my

01:06:02.000 --> 01:06:03.510
opinion based on what I've provably

01:06:03.520 --> 01:06:05.670
built. I use my academic credentials

01:06:05.680 --> 01:06:07.190
because unfortunately that's what a lot

01:06:07.200 --> 01:06:08.789
of people look at. I'm perfectly

01:06:08.799 --> 01:06:10.390
positioned to tell you not to trust

01:06:10.400 --> 01:06:12.630
papers from X conference or Y University

01:06:12.640 --> 01:06:14.710
by default. It's a weak signal at best

01:06:14.720 --> 01:06:16.549
and I've been burned replicating bogus

01:06:16.559 --> 01:06:17.670
results from people who should

01:06:17.680 --> 01:06:19.510
absolutely know better. While less

01:06:19.520 --> 01:06:21.349
common, people do sometimes straight up

01:06:21.359 --> 01:06:23.349
lie to get their work published. More

01:06:23.359 --> 01:06:25.190
often, it's a combination of noisy

01:06:25.200 --> 01:06:26.950
experiments and wishful thinking induced

01:06:26.960 --> 01:06:29.190
by six months of long hours at the lab.

01:06:29.200 --> 01:06:30.789
The best indicator that a work is

01:06:30.799 --> 01:06:32.309
correct is open source code with

01:06:32.319 --> 01:06:33.990
multiple independent replications and

01:06:34.000 --> 01:06:36.230
usage and follow-up work. But this still

01:06:36.240 --> 01:06:37.670
isn't a perfect signal, and I've been

01:06:37.680 --> 01:06:39.430
burned here, too. Replicating the

01:06:39.440 --> 01:06:40.950
results of papers is a great way to

01:06:40.960 --> 01:06:42.470
learn, but know that this can take

01:06:42.480 --> 01:06:45.029
months. Absolutely implement some of the

01:06:45.039 --> 01:06:46.950
more basic papers when learning a new

01:06:46.960 --> 01:06:53.829
area, though.

01:06:57.910 --> 01:06:57.920
do this instead. Look for errors. Assume

01:06:57.920 --> 01:07:00.309
publications are wrong by default and

01:07:00.319 --> 01:07:02.470
find the skeletons in the closet. Are

01:07:02.480 --> 01:07:04.150
the experiments poorly controlled? Are

01:07:04.160 --> 01:07:06.470
the baselines too weak? Is the reasoning

01:07:06.480 --> 01:07:08.230
provided the only plausible explanation

01:07:08.240 --> 01:07:10.390
for the results? Work to decouple the

01:07:10.400 --> 01:07:12.230
content of the paper from its usually

01:07:12.240 --> 01:07:14.309
over complicated presentation. To the

01:07:14.319 --> 01:07:15.910
extent that the paper is correct, how

01:07:15.920 --> 01:07:17.750
does it fit in with surrounding works?

01:07:17.760 --> 01:07:19.510
Building intuition is a combination of

01:07:19.520 --> 01:07:21.589
validating claims and pattern matching.

01:07:21.599 --> 01:07:23.190
You can think of this as estimating the

01:07:23.200 --> 01:07:25.029
probability that a specific direction or

01:07:25.039 --> 01:07:26.950
method is worth your time. The greatest

01:07:26.960 --> 01:07:29.109
opportunity arises or the greatest

01:07:29.119 --> 01:07:31.190
opportunities arise when all the papers

01:07:31.200 --> 01:07:33.190
in a specific area are making the same

01:07:33.200 --> 01:07:34.950
error. This usually happens when the

01:07:34.960 --> 01:07:36.470
premise of a topic or the standard

01:07:36.480 --> 01:07:38.870
evaluations are fundamentally flawed.

01:07:38.880 --> 01:07:40.390
Great researchers can pierce the veil of

01:07:40.400 --> 01:07:42.150
collective myopia to strike out in new

01:07:42.160 --> 01:07:48.710
directions.

